<div class="container_12">
	<div class="grid_8">
		<div class="content-box">
			<h1>HOW-TO INSTALL</h1>
		</div>
		<div class="content-box-white">
			<h2>Where can I download it?</h2>
			<p>Only if you purchased the game, you can download a security
				copy from anywhere. ;-)</p>
			<p class="bold">
				Download link: <a href="http://bit.ly/WU9J8i">Chivalry.Medieval.Warfare-HI2U</a>
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="content-box-white">
			<h2>OK, I have downloaded it, what's next?</h2>
			<p>Now you have to mount it to a virtual drive:
			<ul>
				<li>If you have Windows 8, just double click on the <b>hi-chiva.iso</b>
					and it'll automatically mount the image file
				</li>
				<li>Otherwise, you have to use a third-party program, like <a
					href="https://www.google.hu/search?q=daemon+tools">Daemon Tools</a>
					and mount the <b>hi-chiva.iso</b> image file
				</li>
			</ul>
			</p>
			<p>If you open the drive, you have to see something like that</p>
			<div style="text-align: center">
				<img src="/static/images/install/1.png">
			</div>
			<p>Double click on the setup.exe, and install the game. Just
				click OK, next, next, install, finish...</p>
		</div>
		<div id="update" class="content-box-white">
			<h2>You have to update it!</h2>
			<p class="bold">
				Download link: <a href="http://bit.ly/VjugSt">Chivalry Medieval
					Warfare v1.0.10246.0 Update Patch</a>
			</p>
			<p>
				Now, run the <b>Patch_1.0.10246.0.exe</b>!<br /> <span
					style="font-weight: bold; color: #f82626;">On Windows 7/8
					you have to run it as an administrator!</span>
			</p>
			<div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 10px;">
				<img src="/static/images/install/2.png">
			</div>
			<div style="text-align: center; margin: 10px;">
				<script type="text/javascript">
				<!--
					google_ad_client = "ca-pub-6335041482514787";
					/* banner */
					google_ad_slot = "2014960478";
					google_ad_width = 468;
					google_ad_height = 60;
				//-->
				</script>
				<script type="text/javascript"
					src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js">
					
				</script>
			</div>
			<h2>If this method didn't work, then make a new folder anywhere
				and install the update into it!</h2>
			<p>Then copy the contents of this folder to the installation
				folder:
			<ul>
				<li><b>32 bit Windows:</b> Program Files\Chivalry Medieval
					Warfare</li>
				<li><b>64 bit Windows:</b> Program Files (x86)\Chivalry
					Medieval Warfare</li>
			</ul>
			</p>
			<div style="text-align: center">
				<img src="/static/images/install/2.2.png">
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="content-box-white">
			<h2>I have installed the game, what's next?</h2>
			<p>
				Copy the <b>Multiplayer Fix.exe</b> to this folder:
			<ul>
				<li><b>32 bit Windows:</b> Program Files\Chivalry Medieval
					Warfare\Binaries\Win32</li>
				<li><b>64 bit Windows:</b> Program Files (x86)\Chivalry
					Medieval Warfare\Binaries\Win32</li>
			</ul>
			</p>
			<p>
				Now, run the <b>Multiplayer Fix.exe</b>!</br> <span
					style="font-weight: bold; color: #f82626;">On Windows 7/8
					you have to run it as an administrator!</span>
			</p>
			<div style="text-align: center">
				<img src="/static/images/install/3.png">
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="content-box">
			<h1>Congratulation! You have successfully installed the game!</h1>
		</div>
